    "messageBody": "<div id=\"ygrps-yiv-1247610046\">Hi<br/>\n<br/>\nYou are right we need to test the Business Objects not EJB&#39;s<br/>\n<br/>\nRegards & Thanks<br/>\n<br/>\nRavikumar Chiguruvada<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n                                                                           <br/>\n             &quot;rvdamle&quot;                                                     <br/>\n             &lt;<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:rvdamle@...\">rvdamle@...</a>                                             <br/>\n             m&gt;                                                         To <br/>\n             Sent by:                  <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:junit@yahoogroups.com\">junit@yahoogroups.com</a>               <br/>\n             junit@yahoogroups                                          cc <br/>\n             .com                                                          <br/>\n                                                                   Subject <br/>\n                                       [junit] JUnit and J2EE testing      <br/>\n             04/25/2005 10:29                                              <br/>\n             AM                                                            <br/>\n                                                                           <br/>\n                                                                           <br/>\n             Please respond to                                             <br/>\n             junit@yahoogroups                                             <br/>\n                   .com                                                    <br/>\n                                                                           <br/>\n                                                                           <br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\nHi,<br/>\n<br/>\nOne of our clients have implemented JUnit with EJB&#39;s as follows.<br/>\n<br/>\nJunit code is calling EJB methods ( which directly have DB calls based<br/>\non Hibernate)and then checking DB via hibernate objects.<br/>\nTests are run manually and of course they need container running.<br/>\n<br/>\nIs this the OK this way? Can we call this as unit testing?<br/>\nIdeally I think DB logic should be encapsulated in Business Objects<br/>\nwhich can be tested with JUnit instead of EJBs.<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\nAny thoughts on this?<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\nYahoo! Groups Links</div>", 
